articles.content: Flight status displayed on an information board at the Hong Kong International Airport on July 19, 2025. Wipha was located around 280km south-east of Hong Kong as of midnight, according to Hong Kong’s weather observatory. “There will be frequent heavy squally showers and thunderstorms over the region. Seas will be high with swells,” the observatory added. China’s Hainan and Guangdong provinces were also put on high alert, state news agency Xinhua reported on July 19.
